<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T11:36:00-05:00" n="1082" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1082">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3902.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28T10:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>My April 27. Referring Brazilian Minister’s message, I have again
                            addressed him most urgently that in spite of Foreign Minister’s
                            assurances we are positively informed Americans detained at Cordoba,
                            Aguascalientes and other places and have requested Brazilian Minister
                            again see Foreign Minister reiterating representations in strongest
                            manner, insisting that all Americans be allowed go place of safety under
                            safe conduct. Have also asked Brazilian Legation keep us constantly
                            informed.</p>
                        <p>We are using all means at our disposal secure information that is
                            reliable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>